Dialogs.Dialog: Nene
Beautiful... It's like we're walking through a tunnel painted in pink.
Yeah, that's true.
Did you know？ There's something in cherry blossoms that makes people get drunk easily.
...What？
It's some substance that makes you get drunk. That's why people are in such high spirits during flower viewing.
That story, I feel like I've heard it before...
Really？ Have I told you？
Hm... I don't remember too well.
Hehe. Maybe we're both drunk？
From the cherry blossoms？
Yep. From the cherry blossoms.
Nene
Hey, it'd be nice to be under the shade of that tree.
Okay, let's walk there.
Ah... Wait.
Hehe. I found it~
What？ A cicada's empty shell？
Yeah. When I was a child, I thought this thing was mysterious. It was hollow and it didn't move.
You didn't know that the cicada had grown up and left the shell？
I didn't know that. I thought they were toys shaped like a bug that some kids broke them and threw them away.
lthough there were a lot of them and they were attached to the tree？
Yeah.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, if you were a leading character in a mystery novel, every case would remain unsolved.
Geez. I only thought like that when I was a child.
This is amazing. Everything has turned into yellow.
Nene
There's nothing as impressive when everything is yellow like this.
But this is what we feel during the fall, isn't it？
Yeah, you're right.
Ah, speaking of fall, when you were a kid, did you like to pick up ginkgo nuts under ginkgo trees？
Yeah, I think.
I miss doing that. Fall is the season that reminds you of the past, huh？ It's nostalgia.
Ah, I guess so.
Now, we're walking together like this... I wonder if we will think about this day some time later...
Yeah, I think we will.
It'd be nice if, some day, we can be together like this and think about the past.
Nene
All the leaves have fallen down.
Winter desolation, huh？
Even though they look like this, they still live on. That's why I think they're amazing.
Plants' life forces are really amazing.
Yeah. Among perennial plants, mealy primrose would be the first one to go above ground after winter.
Is that so？
Eh？ Am I wrong？
I can't remember it, though. Anyway, I'm really looking forward to the spring.
I love the winter.
Really？
Yeah. I can keep adhering to you to get warm. It feels good, you know？
Ouch...！
Nene
Ah！ Are you okay！？
I'm fine. I just tripped a little bit... Ouch！
Don't overdo it. Let's take a break.
But...
...Now, your hand.
I'm really okay. I can walk by myself.
I said "Don't overdo it," didn't I？ Come on.
...All right.
Now, let's go.
Okay.
It feels strange to visit the shrine when there are no special festivals.
Nene
Really？ I come here a lot.
Hmm？ Then do you often offer your prayer to the gods？
Yeah. Well... Ah, no. Never mind.
What？ Just say it.
Hmm... Don't laugh, okay？
I won't laugh. I absolutely won't laugh.
Well... Um... I also came here before I went to confess to you.
That's...
Okay, forget it. Pretend you didn't hear it, okay？ Urgh, this is embarrassing.
When I was a kid, I couldn't tell shrines and temples apart.
Nene
Really？ If you see the archways, then it's the shrine.
It's not like that... Well, can you tell the Shinto gods and the Buddha apart...？
I see. But in the past, didn't the Shinto gods and the Buddha co-exist？
Is that so？ Hmm？
Somehow, when Buddhism first came to Japan, people called the Buddha "the Foreign God."
And？
Sorry. That's all I know.
Which means they haven't made this story into a horror movie, right？
Hey, it's not like I'm only interested in horror movies.
Nene
Hmm...
What's wrong？ Wasn't it interesting？
Well... I just couldn't get it. Why didn't the guy chase after his girlfriend then？
Was it strange？
It wasn't strange concerning the whole plot. If he chased after her, they wouldn't love each other so much in the end.
Yeah, it wouldn't become a happy ending then.
But to think about the girl's feelings... It's natural that the guy must chase after her, right？
When you put it that way, I kind of agree with you.
Right！？ He had chosen her already. That's the part I couldn't understand.
Do you always think this much when you watch a movie？
Eh！？ Ah... Yeah, pretty much... Is it strange？
No, I could expect this from ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
Eh？ Ah... What？ Oh no... Geez...
I'm tired...
Nene
What's wrong？ Wasn't it fun？ I really enjoyed it, though...
Well, it was fun, but I feel tired after watching it...
Yeah, the hero was cool and handsome. I can't imagine how he can do all the action scenes.
As a girl, do you find that kind of a macho guy attractive？
Eh？ Ah... Hehehe.
The one that I love is the guy that gets tired from watching an action movie, you know？
Nene
Ah, it was funny. I feel like I haven't laughed that much in a while.
For me, I think ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is funnier.
Eh？ What about me？
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, I don't usually see you laughing out loud like that.
Ah... Did I laugh with my mouth wide open？
Yeah.
No... Oh no. Ah~ Geez.
I'm just kidding. Sorry. Actually you used your hand to cover your mouth and you laughed "Hohohoho" like this.
Urgh... That's... also embarrassing.
It's okay. Even if you laugh out loud, you're still cute.
But you were watching me doing something embarrassing the whole time. Urgh...
Nene
It was fun. I haven't watch animated movies at the theater in a while. Many of them aren't aimed just at kids.
When I watched it, I even forgot that they were just drawings. They looked real and alive.
The word "animate" means "to make alive," don't you know？
Is that so？
The still drawings were made alive by applying motions. That's why they called it animation.
Then today's movie was really well animated.
Yeah, I agree.
Nene
Somehow, it was amazing. I didn't expect it to leave such long-lasting impression to me.
Eh？ It's rare to see you being excited like this.
Yeah. I think I'm up to the intellectual challenge！ It feels good to exercise my brain... I think.
Speaking of which, when I was a kid, I couldn't enjoy sci-fi movies as much as I do now.
Right. When we were kids, we could only enjoy the graphics but we didn't understand the stories.
This is something that you need to grow up enough to understand, huh？
Hehe, I guess so. When we become adults, if we're still together like this, there will be a lot of things await us, right？
I hope there are.
I-It was scary. ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, you seemed to be fine with it.
Nene
Not at all. I was scared.
But then, why do you like horror movies？
Hmm, I like the scary parts, and also the parts where the movie characters have to fight against what they fear.
Hmm... Then you would be scared if it were like a real ghost story？
Ah... I'd be scared. Very scared. That's the real scary thing.
Hmm. But I've heard a very scary story. It's about Kijima-san that...
Noooo！ Noooo！ No way. Stop it！
Ouch...
Ah... I'm sorry！ I just...
No... I'm sorry. Haha...
(▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ was really scared, huh...？)
Yah！
Nene
That's amazing！ You just had 4 strikes in a row！
I just threw it with full strength. Now, it's ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s turn.
Hmm, I don't have the strength, so I'll just try my best with my techniques.
...Your techniques？
My personal techniques to make the ball go right to the pins and hit them.
...That sounds mysterious, huh？
The result is everything. Now, here I go.
(...How did she manage to get a strike from that？)
Nene
Yah！
Ah...
Ah, no！ Not that way！ Turn！ Turn！
A strike！？ From there！？
Aha, saw that！？ How was it？
Wow, how did you make it turn like that...？
Hehehe. Amazing, right？
Yeah, amazing.
It's like a man who traveled around the world, but ended up buying souvenirs from a store next to his house, right？
(Her comparison is even more difficult to understand...)
Nene
I really can't compete with you. I probably have to practice more.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s mysterious throwing techniques are quite amazing for me.
Mysterious throwing techniques...？ Is that praise？
I've never seen something like that before.
Really？ So, you can't see it when you play with others, right？ Do you have fun？
I'm having fun, but... I'm not sure if you enjoy playing it or not...
For me, if you're happy, so am I.
Come on. Let's play one more game.
Nene
Phew...
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, you really got into the groove. That was something.
...But, I'm at my limit. I've used up all my strength.
It seems so. Can you still walk？
Hmm... Seems quite difficult. I'm burnt out.
Hey... Can I lean on you for a bit？
Yeah, sure.
So, just a bit... Just for a moment...
Whoa！ Hey... you're too close...
Hehehe. You don't like it when I do this？
It's not that I hate it...
...Hehe. Thanks for letting me lean on you.
Nene
What do you think？
It was really good...
Great, wasn't it？ It told us more stories than just regular music, right？
Yeah. Now, I think I understand it more.
That's nice to hear. Not many people agree with my thoughts.
Really？
Well, I can't really explain why, but that's how I feel.
I see.
Yeah... Hehehe. I'm a bit happy that I could talk to you about something like this.
Ah, it was fun.
Nene
Hip-hop is really straightforward, right？ Putting rhythmic lyrics to music.
Yeah. I agree.
Hey. Do you know the difference between hip-hop and rap？
Umm... They're both the same, aren't they？
Hehe. Well, hip-hop is a culture, okay？
Is that so？
Yeah. It originated in New York. Rap is a rhythmic style that hip-hop artists use for their music.
You're quite something, knowing info like that.
Hehe, I came prepared.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, are you okay？ Hey, over here.
Nene
Ah... Okay. Phew. We finally got out.
Are you okay？ That was some crowd.
Yeah. I never knew this singer was this popular.
Now that I think about it, I've heard her songs being played all over town.
That's right...
Urgh, I just didn't pay attention.
So, how was the show？
I'm glad I came here even if I didn't have a clue. Now I understand why her albums are selling well.
Me too. Maybe I should grab a copy of her CD, too.
Hehe... Let me know when you go shopping for it. I'll tag along.
Yeah. Sure.
Nene
Ah, that was fun. Now my stomach hurts.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, I don't see you laugh out loud like that often.
Yeah. But it doesn't mean that I'm a gloomy girl. I laugh when it's time to laugh.
I know that. By the way, which act did you think was the funniest？
Let me see... Umm, what does he call himself again？ The guy who talked without end.
That guy was awesome, don't you think？
I wonder how he breathed. I have no idea...
And all those rhyming words he said made it even more amazing.
Yeah. I think it's more difficult to make the audience laugh than to make them cry.
Today, I've learned that you don't necessarily have to make a fool of yourself to make people laugh.
(...Why did you need to learn that？)
Nene
Are you okay？ Do you need a handkerchief？
No, it's okay. I have mine...
You were touched？
Yeah. That was some really nice story.
I guess. They made me laugh so much, but they did make the final part a touching one.
You know, while I was watching the show, I was imagining myself in the heroine's shoes...
Then your boyfriend would be dying？ ...That would be me！
I'm begging you. Please don't die on me, okay？ Please don't leave me behind, okay？
...Okay, I will not die. I must not. I'm not leaving ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
Okay.
Nene
How was it？ Did I sing well？
That was amazing...
I was surprised too. I even remembered the dance moves that I learned in grade school.
I felt like I was watching an old idol TV program. You were amazing.
To think about it, those idols are amazing. They sing and dance and keep smiling to the audience.
It's impossible for me to be an idol.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is already my idol.
Geez, even so, I won't sing or dance for you in public, okay？
Oh, that was nice.
Nene
Hehe... That's all you can say？
Yeah, it was great. ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ really is good at singing.
Is that so？ When you praise me like that, I get embarrassed.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, don't you think you're good at singing？
Huh？...Ah, maybe a little. When I sing, I feel empathy with the lyrics of the songs.
That's right, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. When you sing, I can feel what's in your heart.
That's because... I'm trying to tell you what's in my heart...
...A counterattack？ Now I'm getting embarrassed.
Hehe.
Nene
Hey, do you know this song？
Ah... Yeah, I know it.
Then I'll enter it.
But this is a duet song, isn't it...？
That's why I asked you first. Shall we sing it together？
It's gonna be embarrassing.
It's okay. If you miss a part, I can cover it for you.
That's not the point, though...
Hehe. This feels like a dream, huh？
Nene
Wow... Beautiful. The whole city looks like glasswork...
Ah, look over there. We can see the Bay Bridge too.
Really？ Where？
Ah！ Don't just stand up...！！！！
Kyaa！
Whoa！ Oh！！
T-Thanks...
Are you okay？ Did you get hurt？
Um, well... Aren't I heavy？
I'm fine. Can you stand up？
I can, but...
...But？
Just a little bit... more... I want to stay like this just a little bit more...
Nene
We are almost at the peak.
When we get up there, we'll see the ocean too.
Yeah. Well... Can I go over there？
Yeah, fine. It's gonna sway, so be careful.
Thanks... W-Whoa...
Are you okay？
Um, I'm okay. Huh...？
Hehe...
What？
I can smell your shampoo from here...
Nene
Kyaa！ Ah~ This is scary.
Wait... Don't cling on to me this much...
But... Ah！ Again！
Hey, give me your hand. We will walk hand in hand from this point onward, okay？
Hmm, that's fine.
...Now, I can feel at ease.
This is okay, so...
Kyaa！
Are you okay？
Geez... Why do they keep haunting us like this？
(Because we're in a haunted house. That's why...)
Whoa！
Nene
Calm down. Are you okay！？
I'm not okay. ...Kyaa！
Geez. I didn't expect that it would be this scary. I'm sorry.
...▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ seems to be pretty cool with this.
I'm scared, too... But I can't leave you alone.
I feel ashamed... Let's get out of here！
Come on. Just hold on to me, okay？ We're almost at the exit.
...Thanks.
Whoaaaa！ Hahaha, that is really scary！
Nene
Kyaaa！ We are flying！！
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, are you okay！？
I'm fine！ It's not so scary！
Eh！？ What！？
It's not scary！
I can't hear you！
If I'm with you, I'm not scared of anything！
Sorry. If this stopped, I might be able to hear you！！！！
Hehehe... You idiot.
Nene
Urgh... I was scared. Why do people like this scary thing...？
Wasn't it fun？
No....Maybe a little. It was thrilling.
Yeah. It might've been too intense. Should we ride a relaxing ride next？
But, I don't mind riding this once more.
Since we are already here, that's why.
It can't be...
Let's take this challenge one more time.
(Are you serious！？)
Nene
When I was a child, I didn't feel comfortable with bustling festivals like this.
Hmm？ Why？
Because the night afterwards, when I walked past the shrine that just had the festival...
Ah, you were surprised how it could be so much different from the night before, right？
Yeah. The night before was so bustling, but the shrine after was so dark and quiet that I became scared.
Do you also feel bad for the parade we're watching now？
No, it's fun because you're here with me.
I see.
When you're with me, everything becomes fun.
Nene
Ah, what a pity... Urgh.
What？ You can't see it？
I can't... It's so crowded here that I can't see anything. What should I do？...Just give up？
That would be quite disappointing.
Then... Shall we push ourselves through the crowd to get to the front？
Shall we try that？ Just follow my lead, okay？
Um, got it.
All right！ Let's go！
Hmm, I'll also help by pushing your back.
All right... Just a little bit.
Yay. Are we away from the crowd？
Phew... I'm tired.
You did a nice job.
You can see it from here, right？
Um, I think I've seen something more worthy than the parade. It's your wonderful action.
Oh no... It's so crowded. I guess we can't see anything from here.
Nene
Um, it's okay.
But you really want to watch it, right？ How about I give you a piggyback ride？
I'm fine. You probably can't carry me.
So you don't have confidence in my strength, huh？
Hey, how about we walk over there while everyone else is watching the parade？
...Um, that's okay. But, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, is it really okay with you？
Yeah. For me... as long as I have you by my side, I don't really care much about the parade...
...I see. I got it. Let's go.
Hey... Can we hold hands？
Nene
Do you really want to try that giant slide？
Isn't it gonna be fun？
It's just going straight down to the pool, isn't it？
Yeah, that's why we don't have to worry.
But that's what makes me worried...
Can't I just take a look？
I think it's gonna be fun if we slide down together.
Hmm... Then only once. Just once and it's over, okay？
Thanks！
Geez... You're like a kid.
Nene
No... Water is getting in my nose.
Hmm, it's really impossible. I still can't believe that ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is such a hopeless swimmer.
Ah, hey. How many times are you going to say that？
Hmm... Well, how much do you weigh？
Eh！？ Why did you ask？ Urgh... Lend me your ears.
Okay...
Well...
Considering your weight, you might be able to float in the water.
Really？
Yeah. Fat is lighter than water, so you might be able to float... How's that？
Geez！ You idiot！
Argh！
Nene
Ah, we've been playing a lot. I'm getting a bit tired.
Yeah, I always get tired after swimming. It's like my energy is drained out.
But it feels so good. If I can sleep now, I'll be so happy.
Do you want to sleep？
What if I did？ Would you leave me here and go home by yourself？
No way. How could I do that？
Hehe... That's good to hear.
I'd prefer watching your sleeping face instead.
Ah... Eh？ Ah！ Um, we should go home now. Yeah, I can't sleep here. Yeah...
Nene
There are so many stars...
There might really be space aliens out there.
Yeah... I wouldn't feel surprised if there really were.
There might be some planet that is exactly the same as the earth.
It might have a country that's the same as Japan...
With a city that's the same as this city...
And with someone just the same as you...
Yeah, and someone just the same as ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, too...
They might also be in a planetarium now and are talking about something like this...
That'd be nice.
Yeah. That'd be really nice...
There really are a lot of stars...
Nene
But these are just some of them. There are countless stars that we can't view from the earth.
At one point, 13.7 billion years ago, it all started.
The Big Bang？
Yeah. The universe, the earth, and even us. Everything started from nothing at all.
It took that many billions of years until we met...
In this city.
At the family restaurant.
To think about it, that was quite amazing.
Yeah, amazing.
And... It's quite wonderful.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲... I said, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲！！
Nene
Ah... Hmm... Eh！？ Ah, sorry. Did I fall asleep！？
Yeah. You seemed to enjoy your rest.
Ah, sorry. I was looking at the stars, and somehow I just...
It's all right. Are you okay？ Can you stand up？
I'm fine... Ah, I had such a strange dream.
Dream？ So you were sound asleep.
Yeah. Well, I was Andromeda in my dream. And when I was about to be eaten by a monster, then you...
Was I Perseus？ Did I ride on Pegasus？
No. ...You were riding a raccoon dog.
...No way.
Nene
What if mankind came to an end...？
What is it all of a sudden？
Sorry. It's just my imagination. Like a few years after that, plants would cover everything in the city.
A few years？ Not like 10 or more？
Just a few years. They would also cover the roads and the buildings. Everything.
Do you think so？
Like the garden in my hometown. If we didn't do proper maintenance, the plants would grow everywhere.
If there were no humans, eventually, everything would return to a natural state, huh？
Even if the world became like that, I wouldn't care.
Why？
As long as you're with me now, I'm okay.
Nene
Wow, this is amazing. What is this flower？
Let's see... It's called rebellious spirit. It belongs to the mallow family.
It's huge！ About 20 cm？ Or maybe larger than that.
If you used it as a hair ornament, it'd be so heavy that you might collapse.
Yeah. Ah, if I wanted some hair ornaments, those would be good. Look.
Ah, they're tiny and cute. They even look like white rabbits.
Let me see. The name is... widow bunny？
...Ah. I shouldn't use them.
Why？ They're cute.
But they're carnivorous plant.
...I see.
There are so many plants. Wow, that's an aquatic- plants corner over there.
Nene
The water lilies are beautiful. That lotus's leaf looks like a table.
Ah, there's a frog on that leaf.
No way！
What？
I'm... not very good with frogs...
Is that so？ ...Now, I don't know if I should tell you or not.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, there's another frog near your feet...
Noooo！
Whoa！ Don't jump all of a sudden like that！
Nene
Ah... I was really touched.
Yeah.
I don't usually get a chance to listen to classical music, but it'd be nice to listen to every once in a while.
The music that didn't even have lyrics could make me cry. I think it was a first for me.
It's old, but the good things remain good, huh？
Come to think of it... The songs have been conveyed since many hundred years ago, so that's natural.
What do you mean？
Things that have been passed through generations mean that they have their values, right？
Ah, I see. If people didn't think the songs were good, the songs wouldn't remain until now.
There are reasons for the old things to be passed to the present, okay？
Ah？ That sounds very philosophical.
Hehehe.
The show was very exciting.
Nene
Yeah, right. It was the first time I saw you being in high spirits like that.
The singers were cute. I understand their fans' feeling now.
Eh？ Ah, right. They're cute, huh？
Um, no. I mean they're cute as idols...
I know. They're cute.
But for me, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is much--
Hehehe. I was joking. I also have some guy as my idol, okay？
Who！？
It's a secret♪
(Right, she's still mad！)
Nene
Hmm.
Huh？ It wasn't interesting？
Well, it was interesting, but...
What？
For a musical show, they usually sing abruptly during the play, right？
Sort of. Come to think of it, that's kind of odd.
Yet we didn't think that it was odd at all. It's amazing. It's different from when we hear someone suddenly hums a tune, huh？
Yeah. When I think about it, it's quite amazing.
Shall we try to sing when we talk？
...Better not. It'd be really weird if we actually did that.
Nene
...I was scared.
It was really intense, huh？
Yeah, there were those "bam" and "bang" noises. Did they really hit each other for real？
Hmm, I wonder. I've heard that they might have a script for it...
But the punches and kicks were real, right？ I saw them.
...Even if they had a script for it, I still think that it was a real fight.
I think so too. It's not like they didn't get hurt.
I've seen this on TV, but... somehow... I still feel like I've just watched something amazing.
...I was scared, but I still want to watch it again.
Okay. If we have a chance, all right？
But I think I'll be quite scared, though.
Urgh, this is regrettable. Maybe we didn't cheer for them enough.
Nene
Yeah. But it was a close match, right？ There was just a 1 point difference.
Right. The battle between pitchers like that was really something.
Speaking of which, I used to be batter no. 4 for my school's team when I was in grade school.
Eh？ That was unexpected.
No, actually I was chosen because I was the tallest one in my class. So it wasn't unexpected at all.
How was the game？
I couldn't hit any balls. Three strikes, batter out. I couldn't hit a single ball. Everyone blamed me.
Hmm. But it wasn't ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s fault.
That's why I hate baseball. But, if I come to watch it with you, I feel like I don't hate it that much.
Really？ Then how about we come to watch it again？
Okay. If we have a chance, all right？
It was so crowded... Are you okay？
Nene
Yeah... Just a little exhausted, I think...
I only read some of the comic books' fan works, but there were really a lot of artists here...
Yeah...
So, did you buy anything？
Yeah, some fan circle's books for a movie.
It must be a horror movie, right？
Yeah, this circle has been around for over 20 years.
Do you... plan to buy all the books that have been published during these 20 years？
No way... But I was thinking about that...
(Will it be okay...？)
Nene
Ah, look. We can see the lights from the city.
Ah, that's true. That's wonderful.
For each light we see, someone is there.
Yeah.
We were like the lights that were scattered around everywhere...
Ah... Yeah. But we met each other.
There were so many coincidences... That might be fate, I think.
Yeah, it might be.
But no matter what fate will bring to us, I will never leave your side.
Me neither...
Nene
Ah, what？
The sea birds. What are they...？ Seagulls or black-tailed gulls？
Ah, ah, ah. They're coming this way. Eh？ Ah, what should we do？
Maybe they just want some food, huh？
Eh？ Food？ Well, do I have anything？ Well... Ah.
Got something？
Y-Yeah. Okay, here you go. Eat it. E-Eh...？
Ah, they're gone. What did you give them？
Cough drops.
...Ah. Ahaha.
Nene
Are you scared when you look at the sea at night？
Why？
Hmm... During the day, the water's surface reflects sunlight, and we never know what lies under that surface...
Under the water's surface？
Yeah, right. With this much water, we won't know how deep it goes and there are parts that the sunlight will never reach.
When I think about it, I start to feel scared a bit.
It's like the sea we see during the day isn't its true form... That's why I'm scared of the sea at night.
But isn't that like people？ We have sorrow and anguish. But if we can overcome the pain, life would be wonderful.
Hmm... That's right. I see. That's why the sea during the day looks so beautiful.
Are you still scared of it？
Hmm... I'm still a bit scared... Hmm, but I'm fine now. Thanks.
Okay, I've bought it.
Nene
Ah, thanks. Hehehe.
What？
Well, why are fried noodles at the beach tastier than usual？
I wonder more about why we have fried noodles sold at the beach.
Come to think of it, they always sell noodles at the beach. Why the noodles？
It's mysterious.
